FBIS3-15092 "drsov041_a_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Employee Worked for British Intelligence LD0103145494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1406 GMT 1 Mar 94 LD0103145494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Palariya] [Text] Moscow, 1 Mar -- On 15 January the Federal Counter-Intelligence Service halted the espionage activities of a senior employee at one of Russia's defense-industry enterprises, who had been recruited by the British secret services. Criminal proceedings have commenced, ITAR-TASS was told by the Federal Counter-Intelligence Service. The arrested man was charged on 25 January with betrayal of the homeland, to which he has confessed in full. Preliminary investigations have provided evidence that the accused was provided with special equipment for espionage (ciphers and instructions on how to secretly communicate in Moscow with intelligence at the British embassy). In return for money, the Russian citizen gathered and passed on to the British secret services classified information of a military and economic nature.
